am%2C%20their%20hydroelectric%20project%20built%20on%20the%20Harirud%20River%20in%20a%20remote%20part%20of%20north-western%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20journeyed%20to%20Kabul%20via%20the%20weekly%20scheduled%20flight%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20proceeding%20to%20Herat%20city%20next%20day.%20They%20took%20a%20helicopter%20ride%20to%20the%20dam%20site%2C%20where%20they%20stayed%20for%20three%20days%20before%20embarking%20on%20their%20return%20trip.%20Local%20security%20officials%20and%20representatives%20from%20the%20Afghan%20Ministry%20of%20Energy%20and%20Water%20accompanied%20them%20throughout%20their%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20weathered%20name%20board%20at%20the%20dam%20site%20mirrored%20the%20evolving%20political%20landscape%20in%20Afghanistan.%20Set%20against%20a%20blue%20backdrop%2C%20the%20inscription%20%E2%80%9CAfghan%20India%20Friendship%20Dam%E2%80%9D%20remained%20prominently%20displayed%2C%20while%20several%20other%20lines%20had%20gradually%20faded.%20On%20top%2C%20the%20colours%20of%20the%20Indian%20flag%20remained%20vibrant%2C%20accompanied%20by%20the%20symbol%20of%20entwined%20hands.%20But%20the%20tricolour%20flag%20of%20the%20Afghan%20republic%20along%20the%20same%20line%20seemed%20to%20have%20been%20deliberately%20defaced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20understood%20that%20the%20Taliban%20government%20has%20made%20repeated%20requests%20to%20Indian%20authorities%20for%20the%20dispatch%20of%20a%20technical%20team%20to%20address%20longstanding%20issues%20at%20Salma%20Dam.%20However%2C%20responding%20to%20these%20appeals%20has%20been%20delayed%20amid%20diplomatic%20complexities.%20This%20is%20likely%20the%20first%20visit%20by%20any%20Indian%20official%20delegation%20to%20Afghanistan%20related%20to%20infrastructure%20projects%20since%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25105925%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-22-at-20.56.52-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25105925%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-22-at-20.56.52-1.jpeg%201000w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25105925%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-22-at-20.56.52-1-300x225.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698740%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Indian%20technical%20team%20at%20Salma%20Dam.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20like%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20international%20community%2C%20India%20does%20not%20officially%20recognise%20the%20Taliban%20government%20in%20Afghanistan.%20However%2C%20since%20Indian%20diplomats%20returned%20to%20Kabul%20in%202022%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ftaliban-india-kabul-regional-conference-afghanistan%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNew%2520Delhi%253A%2520India%2520on%2520Monday%2Cconvened%2520in%2520the%2520Afghanistan%2520capital.%5C%22%3Egradual%20build-up%20of%20engagement%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20Taliban%2C%20despite%20the%20stationed%20diplomats%20being%20formally%20designated%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fafghanistan-indian-embassy-technical-team%5C%22%3Etechnical%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%20focusing%20on%20humanitarian%20assistance.%20The%20Taliban%20has%20also%20turned%20towards%20regional%20countries%20as%20prospects%20of%20formal%20diplomatic%20recognition%20from%20the%20UN%20are%20dim%20due%20to%20the%20educational%20restrictions%20on%20women%20and%20girls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fthe-story-behind-herats-salma-dam%5C%22%3EThe%20Amazing%20Indian%20Story%20Behind%20Herat%E2%80%99s%20Salma%20Dam%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20Afghanistan%E2%80%99s%20two%20decade-long%20republic%20era%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20active%20presence%20in%20the%20country%20was%20anchored%20on%20its%20development%20assistance%20totalling%20over%20%242%20billion.%20In%20that%20sphere%2C%20Salma%20Dam%2C%20later%20renamed%20the%20India-Afghanistan%20Friendship%20Dam%2C%20has%20a%20premier%20position%20along%20with%20the%20Afghan%20parliament%20building%20and%20Zaranj%20Delaram%20highway%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20390px)%2085vw%2C%20390px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25110021%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-24-at-23.09.55.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22390%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25110021%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-24-at-23.09.55.jpeg%20540w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25110021%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-24-at-23.09.55-135x300.jpeg%20135w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25110021%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-24-at-23.09.55-461x1024.jpeg%20461w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698741%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22867%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20latest%20view%20from%20top%20of%20the%20dam%20towards%20the%20power%20house%20and%20the%20river.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20appointed%20state-run%20Wapcos%20to%20execute%20the%20project%2C%20the%20state%20firm%20contracted%20the%20construction%20to%20a%20joint%20venture%20of%20two%20private%20firms%2C%20SSJV%20and%20Angelique%20limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInaugurated%20jointly%20by%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20then%20Afghan%20President%20Ashraf%20Ghani%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2Fnewsite%2Fprintrelease.aspx%3Frelid%3D145967%5C%22%3Ein%20June%202016%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20is%20the%20first%20major%20water%20infrastructure%20project%20in%20modern%20Afghanistan%20in%20the%20last%2050%20years.%20The%20project%20was%20also%20diplomatically%20sensitive%20as%20Iran%20had%20objected%20to%20its%20construction%20over%20concerns%20that%20water%20flow%20in%20the%20river%20that%20crossed%20over%20into%20Iranian%20territory%20would%20reduce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20decade%2C%20amidst%20the%20challenges%20posed%20by%20precarious%20security%20conditions%20and%20logistical%20intricacies%2C%20the%20project%20endured%2C%20demanding%20a%20ballooning%20expenditure%20of%20Rs%201775.69%20crore%20(%24265%20million%20in%202016%20exchange%20rate)%20to%20reach%20completion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELinked%20to%20Herat%20city%20by%20a%20165-kilometre%20earthen%20road%2C%20traversable%20only%20under%20escort%20of%20a%20large%20convoy%20of%20security%20personnel%2C%20the%20journey%20consumed%20seven%20to%20eight%20arduous%20hours.%20However%2C%20as%20the%20security%20landscape%20progressively%20deteriorated%20in%20the%20project%E2%80%99s%20final%20years%2C%20all%20ground%20travel%20was%20abruptly%20barred%2C%20compelling%20Indian%20workers%20at%20the%20site%20to%20rely%20solely%20on%20helicopters%20for%20transportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20its%20commissioning%2C%20the%20dam%20was%20handed%20over%20to%20Afghan%20engineers%20and%20technicians%20who%20had%20been%20trained%20in%20India.%20Over%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20teams%20from%20Wapcos%20made%20occasional%20visits%20to%20the%20dam%20for%20inspections%20to%20address%20initial%20operational%20challenges.%20Meanwhile%2C%20in%20India%2C%20the%20main%20contractor%20sued%20Wapcos%20for%20non-payment%20of%20dues%20of%20over%20hundreds%20of%20crores%20in%20a%20case%20that%20has%20to%20be%20still%20resolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20Taliban%20started%20to%20relentlessly%20press%20their%20military%20blitzkrieg%20in%202021%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.khaama.com%2Ftaliban-kill-16-security-personnel-near-salma-dam%2F%5C%22%3Efighting%20became%20increasingly%20closer%20to%20the%20site%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20July%202021%2C%20Taliban%20entered%20Chisti%20Sharif%2C%20the%20nearest%20town%20to%20the%20dam%2C%20and%20damaged%20the%20complex%20of%20rooms%20that%20Wapcos%20had%20built%20for%20staff%20during%20the%20construction%20phase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDevirupaM%2Fstatus%2F1426127389197692932%5C%22%3EOn%20August%2013%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20local%20Taliban%20commander%20entered%20the%20dam%20complex%20after%20the%20soldiers%20surrendered%20following%20the%20Friday%20prayers.%20Soon%2C%20the%20white%20and%20black%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fdevirupam%2Fstatus%2F1427243280652283909%5C%22%3ETaliban%20flag%20fluttered%20over%20the%20dam%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20after%2C%20President%20Ghani%20and%20his%20aides%20fled%20to%20Uzbekistan%2C%20allowing%20the%20Taliban%20to%20seize%20control%20of%20Kabul%20and%20the%20entire%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fexclusive-surrounded-by-taliban-india-built-salma-dams-future-is-uncertain%5C%22%3ESurrounded%20by%20Taliban%2C%20India-Built%20Salma%20Dam%E2%80%99s%20Future%20is%20Uncertain%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20many%20of%20the%20Afghan%20engineers%20had%20migrated%20abroad%20in%20those%20uncertain%20days%2C%20the%20challenge%20in%20the%20new%20Taliban%20era%20was%20to%20find%20trained%20manpower%20to%20operate%20the%20hydropower%20project.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20attrition%20had%20begun%20months%20prior%20to%20the%20Taliban%E2%80%99s%20assumption%20of%20power%2C%20as%20salary%20payments%20dwindled%20owing%20to%20the%20Afghan%20government%E2%80%99s%20revenue%20constraints.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25105817%2Fsalma-dam-wapcos-staff-quarters-2022-photo.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25105817%2Fsalma-dam-wapcos-staff-quarters-2022-photo.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25105817%2Fsalma-dam-wapcos-staff-quarters-2022-photo-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25105817%2Fsalma-dam-wapcos-staff-quarters-2022-photo-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698739%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%202022%20photo%20showing%20the%20damaged%20Wapcos%20accommodation%20in%20Chisti%20Sharif.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20technical%20team%20from%20Wapcos%20has%20gone%20with%20a%20list%20of%20items%20that%20needed%20to%20be%20assessed.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20SCADA%20system%2C%20which%20is%20the%20centralised%20software%20for%20controlling%20the%20dam%2C%20has%20not%20been%20working%20for%20years.%20So%20that%20is%20on%20the%20agenda%20for%20inspection%2C%E2%80%9D%20%C2%A0explained%20a%20source%2C%20who%20did%20not%20want%20to%20be%20named%20as%20he%20is%20not%20authorised%20to%20speak%20to%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20automatic%20mechanism%20for%20opening%20and%20shutting%20the%20irrigation%20sluice%20gates%20have%20been%20out%20of%20action.%20Besides%2C%20several%20instruments%20were%20also%20on%20the%20check%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20their%20three-day%20stay%2C%20the%20team%2C%20which%20includes%20specialists%20in%20geology%2C%20software%20and%20electrical%20systems%2C%20will%20return%20to%20Kabul%20for%20talks%20with%20Afghan%20ministry%20officials.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20the%20best%20time%20to%20inspect%20the%20dam%20as%20the%20water%20level%20is%20at%20its%20lowest%20as%20it%20is%20winter%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20informed%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20their%20stay%20at%20the%20dam%2C%20the%20Indian%20officials%20lived%20in%20the%20camp%20accommodation%20constructed%20by%20another%20Indian%20public%20sector%20company%2C%20BHEL%20for%20their%20technicians%20during%20construction%2C%20as%20the%20Wapcos%20quarters%20remain%20in%20a%20bombed%20out%20condition%20%E2%80%93%20a%20testimony%20to%20the%20tumultuous%20history%20that%20Salma%20dam%20has%20weathered.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708839332000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25105713%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-22-at-20.56.52.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffor-first-time-in-taliban-era-indian-technicians-return-to-inspect-265-million-dam-in-afghanistan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Wire%20has%20learned%20that%20a%20four-member%20team%20from%20the%20Indian%20public%20sector%20company%20Wapcos%20is%20currently%20visiting%20Salma%20Dam%2C%20their%20hydroelectric%20project%20built%20on%20the%20Harirud%20River%20in%20a%20remote%20part%20of%20north-western%20Afghanistan.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffor-first-time-in-taliban-era-indian-technicians-return-to-inspect-265-million-dam-in-afghanistan%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mexican%20president's%20eldest%20son%20denounces%20publication%20of%20his%20phone%20number%2C%20says%20threats%20received%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708838175000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107980838%2Cimgsize-931053.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fmexican-president